If you want to starting reading the remote file from a certain offset, use [`FTPClient.setRestartOffset`](https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-net/apidocs/org/apache/commons/net/ftp/FTPClient.html#setRestartOffset(long)). The FTP server needs to support `REST` command (most do).

    ftp.setRestartOffset(offset);
    InputStream in = ftp.retrieveFileStream(remote_file_name);
    // Now you can read as many bytes as you need from &#39;in&#39;

If you do not want to read the file to the end, and you want to reuse the connection for other operations, you need to call [`FTPClient.abort`](https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-net/apidocs/org/apache/commons/net/ftp/FTPClient.html#abort()).

---

*(You cannot convert `InputStream` to `RandomAccessFile`, nor use `RandomAccessFile` anyhow with files on FTP server)*

