Alternately, you may want a dynamic width.\
For that, you&#39;ll need to first find the value with the most digits.

You can use a _loop_.

```java
int m = String.valueOf(numbers[0]).length();
for (int i = 1, v, n = numbers.length; i &lt; n; i++)
    if ((v = String.valueOf(numbers[i]).length()) &gt; m)
        m = v;
```

Or, a _stream_.

```java
int m = IntStream.of(numbers)
                 .map(x -&gt; String.valueOf(x).length())
                 .max()
                 .getAsInt();
```

Then, build the _format_ string.\
I&#39;m using _+1_ to create a space between the values.

```java
System.out.printf((&quot;%&quot; + (m + 1) + &quot;d&quot;), numbers[i]);
```

